snippet.textDisplay: After having heard Zaved Bashir sir's 'o rangrez and aaj ibbadat' I have become an ardent fan of his BUT here Akbar Ali tops it...waah.. waah...waah Kya baat hai... Melody, classical, soulful..you name it and you have it. Hearing it for the first time today and god knows how many more times I'll hear it...I still remember Akbar Ali sir singing 'koi gata mai so jata' in Junoon...it was just mesmerizing and not to mention his classical rendition in front of the great pandit Hari Prasad Chaurasiya ji. His adab and respect for pandit ji was just impeccable. You are flawless...

snippet.textDisplay: I like this song for having touch of classical. It gives me a feel like i'm a music critic slowly banging my heads to its beats, waving my hands in the air while closing my eyes. This is not classical music but I like the pretense. I know why this song lack views. Its Javed Bashir. While Akbar Ali's voice melts in my ear like butter Javed Bashir is pure energy with heart it is also evident that a lot of people do not like the type of Voice Javed Bashir has. Same thing happened with last season's 'Jhalliya'. That song I think was one of the best compositions of last season but also did not get much attention. Right at the beginning of this song Javed Bashir puts many of them off. Also the classical tone and the 10 mins playtime is also not for everyone I think. But my god what this song do not have I don't know!!! The two vocals are amazing at showing the highs and lows they can touch while making waves at the surface. I will keep it in my loop for some days until all fascination wears off.
